HIV / AIDS: China ta ce an samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 a cikin sabon kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ce yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya ƙaru da kashi 14 cikin ɗari.
Hukumomin kiwon lafiya a kasar Sin sun ce mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar.
An samu kusan mutane 40,000 da suka kamu da cutar a cikin kwata na biyu na 2018.
Yawancin waɗanda suke da wannan cuta sun kamu da cutar ta jima'i, kuma hakan sabon abu ne.
A tarihi, cutar ta bazu cikin sauri a wasu sassan ƙasar sakamakon ƙarin jini da aka yi wa mutane.
Amma, an rage yawan mutanen da ke kamuwa da cutar HIV ta wannan hanyar zuwa kusan babu, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro da aka gudanar a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a kowace shekara, adadin mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV da AIDS a ƙasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
A cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin, kamuwa da cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce.
An dakatar da jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna bambanci ga 'yan LGBT.
Domin ra'ayin mutanen da ba sa son yin jima'i, wasu bincike sun nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da mata da suke son yin jima'i suna aure.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka suna faruwa ne domin ba a kāre su ba ta wurin yin jima'i.
A matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin da gwamnatin Sin take yi na magance wannan matsalar, tun daga shekara ta 2003, ta yi alkawarin samun damar yin amfani da magungunan HIV a ko'ina.
